<HEAD>
<TITLE>Program Information and Benefits</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<img src="/sbsc/sbsmall.gif">
<P>
<center>
<h2>
 Program Information and Benefits<BR>
</h2>
</center>
<P>
<blockquote>
As a SBS Coalition member, your organization will actively participate
in activities and programs that will bring about true positive
change for America's millions of small business owners.  <BR>

<P>
You will be kept abreast of congressional activity through the
Small Business Hill Alert -- a fax update and action alert on
key small business issues being debated and acted upon on Capitol
Hill.  And, twice-monthly (or as needed) SBS Coalition members
will discuss the latest legislative developments through conference
calls with members of Congress, political and policy leaders.
<BR>

<P>
SBS Coalition members will receive an invitation to the annual
National Small Business Summit.  The conference is an annual meeting
featuring hundreds of business leaders setting America's small
business action plan and agenda for economic growth.  Attendees
will hear from members of congress, policy experts, and others
who share a positive vision for American business.<BR>

<P>
Members will also be asked to participate in coalition letters,
congressional testimony, and SBS Coalition's media program.  And
finally, access to SBSC special reports, publications, issue analyses,
congressional testimony, articles, op-eds and other materials
for background and intellectual ammunition is always available
for coaltion members.<BR>

<P>
<a href="/sbsc/coalition/sbscapp.html">Join the Small Business Survival Coalition</a>
<P>
<a href="/sbsc/coalition/sbsc3.html">More Information</a>
<P>
Questions? - <a href="mailto:rstikes2sbsc.org">rstikes@sbsc.org</a><BR>
</blockquote>
