<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>Town Hall Spotlight: Elections & Governing Updates</TITLE>

</HEAD>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/paper2.jpg">  
<P>

<CENTER>
<img src="/townhall/spotlights/elections/spot.gif">
<br><H2>Elections & Governing Updates</CENTER></H2>

The 1996 campaigns are underway and Town Hall will be bringing you the latest information from the campaign trail.  Check here often for the latest poll numbers, press releases, and candidate information.
<i>
 If you are interested in having your information posted here, send your press release to <a href="mailto:jgarth@townhall.com">jgarth@townhall.com</a>. <b>Priority is given to documents already in HTML format.
</b></i>
<P>

<P>
<P>
<P>
<HR>
<P><a name="week"></a>
<center><h3>Check out Heritage's new <a href="/heritage/issues96/tblcon.html">Issues '96</a>! The Candidate's Briefing Book </h3><p>
<b>Do the polls really matter? View the latest Presidential and Senate race <a href="http://www.townhall.com/townhall/spotlights/elections/senate96.html">poll numbers</a> from around the country and decide for yourself.<p></b></center> 

<p>
<b>Campaign Connections</b>
<ul>

<li><b>Arizona</b>: 
<a href="http://www.bundgaard.com/scott">Scott Bundgaard</a> is a Republican State Representative who is running for the State Senate unopposed. CONTACT: <a href="mailto:scott@bundgaard.com">scott@bundgaard.com</a>.<p>
 
<li><b>Arkansas</b>:
1st Congressional District: Mr. Tim Cain is a conservative Republican who is running for Justice of the Peace.<p>

<li><b>California</b>:
<ul><li>1st Congressional District: Republican Congressman <a href="http://redwood.northcoast.com/~riggs">Frank Riggs</a> is running for reelection.<p> 
<li>3rd Congressional District: Conservative Republican candidate <b>Tim LeFever</b> is running against Democrat incumbent Vic Fazio. CONTACT: <a href="mailto:LeFever96@aol.com">LeFever96@aol.com</a> or call 916-678-1994<p>
<li><a href="http://home.aol.com/DCWright96">Debra Wright</a> is running in the ninth district to unseat ultra-liberal Ron Dellums in the fall election.<p>
<li>18th Congressional District: A conservative candidate, Bill Conrad, is running against incumbent Democrat Gary Condit. Contact: <a href="mailto:CONRAD96@aol.com">CONRAD96@AOL.COM</a> or call (209) 549-8573.<p>	
<li>33rd Congressional District: pro-life candidate <a href="http://users.aol.com/ca33gop/private/ca33gop.html">John P. Leonard</a><p>
<li>36th Congressional District: former mayor <a href="http://www.netVIP.com/brooks96/">Susan Brooks</a> is "bringing government home in 1996" <p>
<li>42nd Congressional District: pro-life <a href="http://www1.primenet.com/~wilde/">Judge Linda Wilde</a> is running against liberal Rep. George Brown.<p>
</ul>
<li><b>Colorado</b>: 2nd Congressional District: pro-life candidate <a href="http://www.qadas.com/miller_for_congress/index.html">Pat Miller</a> is running against liberal Democrat David Skaggs. She ran against him in 1994 and nearly defeated him.<p>
<li>Joe Rogers is taking on Liberal Congresswoman Pat Schroeder in Colorado's First Congressional District. His website is located at <a href="http://www.joerogers.com">www.joerogers.com</a>
</ul>
<li><b>Delaware</b>: 
<ul><li><a href="http://www.bdsnet.com/~mike_zeglen">Mike Zeglen</a> is running as the Republican candidate for 19th District State Senate seat. <p>
