<HEAD>

<TITLE>Town Hall Spotlight: The Food and Drug Administration</TITLE>

</HEAD>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/paper2.jpg">  
<P>

<CENTER><a name="intro"></a> 

<H2>The Food and Drug Administration<BR></CENTER></H2>
The Food and Drug Administration was created in 1906 to protect Americans from unsafe food and drugs, but over the years, burdensome FDA regulations have slowed the approval process for many breakthrough medical treatments.  This session, the Congress is beginning to address these concerns and FDA reform is beginning to take shape.  Follow the Spotlight this week as we look at what the FDA does and why it should be reformed.
<P>


<P>
<P>


<HR>

<P><a name="week"></a>

<CENTER><b><a name="Misc">The FDA</a></b> <br>

<a href="#intro">(Introduction)</a></center><p>

<p>
<ul>
<li>Check out the <a href="http://www.fda.gov/">FDA</a> Home Page
<LI>Read about the Progress and Freedom Foundation's <a href="/pff/medical.html">
Medical Innovation Project</a>

<li>Check out the <a href="http://www.fdli.org/">The Food and Drug Law Institute</a> Web Site
<li>Read <a href="/heritage/puns_library/taxation/190112.htm">Regulatory Relief or Power Grab: Should Congress Expand FDA's Enforcement Authority</a>, Backgrounder #900, The Heritage Foundation
<li>Read Michael Fumento's Column, <a href="/townhall/columnists/fume1011.html">Fatheads at FDA Opposing Best Interests of Fat America</a>
<li>Read <a href="/pff/project/tl-1019.html">End the FDA Approval Monopoly"</a> by Thomas M. Lenard
<LI>Read the Vice President's plan to <a href="http://www.fda.gov/po/reinvent.html">reinvent the FDA</a>
</ul>
<P>
