<head>
<title>Education Survey Results</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/paper2.jpg">
<h2><center>Education Survey Results</h2></center>
<hr>
<b>Question:</b> Do you favor eliminating the Dept. of Education?<P>

Yes: 83%<br>
No: 17%<P>

<b>Question:</b> If the Dept. of Education were eliminated, should the money saved be transfered to local schools rather that used for tax or deficit relief?<P>

Yes: 46%<br>
No: 54%<P>

<b>Question:</b> Do you support an educational voucher program which would provide monetary assistance to parents for use at the school of their choice?<P>

Yes: 83%<br>
No: 17%<P>

<b>Question:</b> Do you favor allowing students enrolled in low performing schools to receive state scholarships to attend any accredited school, public or private, into which they are accepted?<P>

Yes: 63%<br>
No: 37%<p>

<b>Question:</b> Do you support tuition tax credits?<P>

Yes: 83%<br>
No: 17%<p>

<b>Question</b> Do you favor reinstating voluntary school prayer?<p>

Yes: 81%<br>
No: 19%<p>

<b>Question</b> Should the public school system be replaced by private schools?<p>

Yes: 50%<br>
No: 50%<p>

</body>
</html>

